        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 12:44AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1243 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Montgomery, or 16 miles west of Willis, moving east at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crabbs Prairie, Huntsville, Dobbin, Montgomery, New Waverly,
Anderson, Dacus, Plantersville, Willis, Huntsville State Park, Lake
Conroe Dam, Roans Prairie, Richards, Riverside, Navasota, and
Trinity.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
southeastern Texas.</instruction>
